Gemma-4 MTP (frozen-KV) patch for container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly.

Cherry-picks upstream SGLang PR #24436 ("Gemma 4 — Adding MTP support"),
merged into `main` on 2026-05-07 — two days AFTER the v0.5.11 release tag.
Without this patch SGLang v0.5.11 has no MTP drafter for Gemma-4: it
promotes `--speculative-algorithm NEXTN` to EAGLE and tries to load the
`google/gemma-4-{26B-A4B,31B}-it-assistant` checkpoints through the
generic Transformers bridge, which then fails with
  ValueError: Unrecognized configuration class
    <...Gemma4AssistantConfig> for this kind of AutoModel: AutoModel.
or, after working around that, with
  ValueError: No module or parameter named 'model.language_model'
    in TransformersMultiModalForCausalLM.

PR #24436 adds:
  - new SGLang-native `Gemma4AssistantForCausalLM` (models/gemma4_mtp.py),
    bypassing the Transformers bridge entirely.
  - `FROZEN_KV_MTP` speculative algorithm + dedicated worker
    (speculative/frozen_kv_mtp_*.py — 5 new files).
  - auto-promote of `--speculative-algorithm NEXTN`/`EAGLE` →
    `FROZEN_KV_MTP` when the drafter's config.architectures contains
    `Gemma4AssistantForCausalLM` (server_args.py).
  - `gemma4_assistant` model_type alias for `gemma4` SWA remap
    (utils/hf_transformers/config.py).
  - `get_embed_and_head()` for both gemma4_causal and gemma4_mm so the
    new MTP worker can share the target's embed/head weights.

Total surface: 11 files changed, 6 NEW (1849 LoC), 5 MODIFIED (~110 LoC).
The patch is upstream-merged → no maintenance debt; it disappears
naturally on the next SGLang version bump (v0.5.12+).

Applies cleanly against v0.5.11 with only small hunk offsets
(verified by `patch --dry-run -p1`). Applied UNCONDITIONALLY (no
*gemma4*-only gate) because the new files are inert until
`--speculative-algorithm FROZEN_KV_MTP` or a Gemma-4 drafter is loaded;
the modifications to spec_info.py / server_args.py only add new branches
to existing dispatchers. Safe for non-Gemma-4 workloads.

Anchor choice: this Dockerfile patch uses the three `# Install sglang
package` comment lines + the `RUN --mount=... uv pip install` line as
context. Those four lines are introduced by dockerfile-sm121.patch and
are unique in the Dockerfile. The optional dockerfile-gemma4-nvfp4.patch
inserts above the same block but uses the upstream `fi` ← boundary as
its anchor (lines well above us). Therefore the two patches never
contend for the same anchor and can be applied in either order.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly AFTER
dockerfile-sm121.patch.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -281,6 +281,18 @@
 # Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
 # Moved here from its original early-stage location so the installed
 # dist-packages picks up the patched nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh above.
+# (Cherry-pick of upstream PR #24436 below adds Gemma-4 MTP support, also
+#  picked up by the same `uv pip install ./python`.)
+COPY patches/sglang-gemma4-mtp-pr24436.patch /tmp/sglang-gemma4-mtp-pr24436.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    echo "=== Applying sglang-gemma4-mtp-pr24436.patch (upstream PR #24436) ===" && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sglang-gemma4-mtp-pr24436.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sglang-gemma4-mtp-pr24436.patch && \
+    test -f python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mtp.py && \
+    test -f python/sglang/srt/speculative/frozen_kv_mtp_worker.py && \
+    grep -q 'FROZEN_KV_MTP' python/sglang/srt/speculative/spec_info.py && \
+    echo 'Gemma-4 MTP (PR #24436) cherry-pick applied successfully'
+
 RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
     uv pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps ./python

